# No Cursor Branding in Project Content

Never introduce references to the **Cursor IDE/product**, **Cursor Agent**, **cursoragent**, **`Co-authored-by: Cursor`** commit trailers, or **cursor.com** email addresses in tracked files, commits, or generated content.

## Scope

Applies to docs, README, markdown, HTML portal pages, code comments, commit messages, deployment docs, partner docs, and release notes. Do not mention Cursor tooling in tracked files (e.g. do not add `/.cursor/` to `.gitignore` to advertise the IDE).

## Do not add

- Product mentions: "Built with Cursor", "Generated by Cursor Agent"
- Attribution: `Co-authored-by: Cursor <agent@cursor.com>` or similar trailers
- Docs framing work as "Cursor-assisted" or linking to cursor.com for authorship

## Exceptions (not violations)

- CSS `cursor: pointer` and Tailwind `cursor-*` utilities
- PHP/database `$cursor` variables for date or result-set iteration
- Third-party metadata in lock files (e.g. composer.lock keyword `"cursor"`) — do not edit lock files for this

## Examples

```markdown
<!-- BAD -->
This guide was written with Cursor Agent.

<!-- GOOD -->
This guide covers EIS Bridge certification steps.
```

```
# BAD commit message trailer
Co-authored-by: Cursor <agent@cursor.com>

# GOOD — no IDE co-author trailer
```

```css
/* GOOD — styling, not product branding */
.btn { cursor: pointer; }
```

When editing existing Cursor references in docs, remove or rephrase neutrally unless the user explicitly asks to keep them.
